Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: Camilo Cienfuegos (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that after his movement's victory in the Cuban Revolution, television broadcasts showed Camilo Cienfuegos (pictured) freeing parrots from birdcages, declaring that the birds had "a right to liberty"?

entry.title: Shakespeare garden in Wessington Springs, South Dakota (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the Shakespeare garden in Wessington Springs, South Dakota, was the first of its kind in the state?

entry.title: Mihail Moxa (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that in the first Romanian universal chronicle, Mihail Moxa shows "the God of the Old and New Testaments baptizing His stars with the names of Olympian deities"?

entry.title: Rodney, Mississippi (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Rodney, Mississippi, became a ghost town after the Mississippi River shifted about two miles (3.2 km) away?

entry.title: Wayne Jacobs (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Wayne Jacobs said that without football he would have been "dead by 30, or in prison"?

entry.title: a Holocaust memoir translated in 2023 (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a Holocaust memoir translated in 2023 described prisoners so dehumanized by the Nazis that they introduced themselves in past tense, as in "My name was ..."?

entry.title: a Taylor Swift song (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a Taylor Swift song shares its name with a recurring refrain from Slaughterhouse-Five?

entry.title: Robert L. McLeod (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Centre College co-president Robert L. McLeod served for fifteen months on a U.S. Navy aircraft carrier while Robert J. McMullen, the other co-president, ran the school's day-to-day operations?

entry.title: a Japanese island (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a Japanese island has rapidly fluctuated in size?
